Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and bilirubinuria, with low urine specific gravity and low HbA1c. These findings suggest impaired renal function, possible nephrotic syndrome, and abnormal glucose/ketone handling not explained by diabetes. Urine appearance and color are abnormal, but no evidence of infection. Further nephrological evaluation and assessment for underlying metabolic or hepatic disorders are recommended.
